  --- Resolution ---
  P55 and P_gate are NOT contradictory:
  - P55: scaling ALL dims of h_final by same factor -> argmax unchanged
    (because softmax is scale-invariant: softmax(ax) = softmax(x))
  - E_gate: changing RELATIVE per-layer contributions -> h_final changes
    (different layers contribute to different directions in h_final)
  - The key quantity is not ||h|| but the DIRECTION of each delta-h
  - E_gate changes which directions get amplified vs suppressed
  - P55 changes the overall magnitude but keeps all relative directions
  Conclusion: Semantic encoding is in the PATTERN of layer contributions,
  not in the total magnitude.

